'''''Win or Die''''' was a highly successful [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Propaganda/Legends|propaganda]] [[Holodrama/Legends|holodrama]]. It starred [[Garik Loran|Garik "Face" Loran]], as a boy who ardently supported the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]] in spite of his [[Parent/Legends|parents]]' opposition. At the story's climax, the boy is shot in the back by his father as he runs to [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. The boy begs the Emperor to rid [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] of evil people like his parents, then dies in Palpatine's arms.

It was believed that this holodrama increased [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial military]] recruitment by five percent. As a reward for his role, Loran was brought to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] to meet the real [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] Palpatine in person. However, the Emperor was unavailable, enraged by new reports of the emerging [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance's]] increasing effectiveness, and Loran instead met with [[Ysanne Isard]], sitting in her lap. He later described this as one of the most revolting experiences of his life. Ironically, Loran would later join the Rebel Alliance.

